    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>White, sweet-tasting, crystalline sugar alcohol which occurs naturally in many plants and algae. Mannitol is used widely as a dietary supplement and dietetic sweetener. In conservation, mannitol is used in tandem with sucrose for impregnation of waterlogged wood. </Note_Text>
